The paper proposes a test based on the theory of algorithmic complexity and an experimental evaluation of Levin's universal distribution to identify evidence in support of or in contravention of the claim that the world is algorithmic in nature. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category. The paper also involves statistical comparison of frequency distributions of data from physical sources and purely algorithmic means, which suggests that it could also belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Computational Complexity (cs.CC), Cryptography and Security (cs.CR), and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories.
